commitResults.messageTitle: Add studentNumber field to Student class
commitResults.messageBody:
The Student class doesn't have a student number field, which is
considered important information to have for tutors to uniquely
identify each student.

Let's add a student number field and update other classes
where necessary.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Parser and AddCommand and its related classes
commitResults.messageBody:
The parser and add command doesn't take into account the new argument
student number when adding a new student to the system since it was a
new field added for Student class.

Let's
* add the student number prefix and rename the student name prefix
* add the argument student number to AddCommand
* implement the prefixes into the parser, command, and test classes
* rename the command word to "add_student"

Update the index to be group specific for Mark Task Command and Delete Task from Group
commitResults.messageBody:
In the MarkTask and DeleteTaskFromGroup commands, they have an index
parameter that refers to the task to update. Previously,
the execute method for both commands made the index refer to the
position of the task in a list of all tasks globally instead of the
position in a list of tasks for a specific group.

Since being group specific is more intuitive as there is also a
parameter for a group name, the index now refers to the position of a
task in a list of tasks for a specific group.

Update task in Group's set of tasks for MarkTask Command
commitResults.messageBody:
When calling MarkTaskCommand, it updated the status of the task in the
list of all tasks, but not in the group specific list of tasks. This
causes the status change to not be reflected when listing out the tasks
for a specific group.

Let's update the command to change the status for both the global and
group-specific list of tasks.
